President Muhammadu Buhari has urged the Nigeria Police Force (NPF) to ensure that the 2019 general election is conducted peacefully. Speaking at the commissioning of 602 Regular Cadet Course One at Police Academy Wudil, Kano on Thursday, Buhari said it was the duty of police to secure the 2019 election. “You must do everything possible to make the 2019 general elections hitch-free. You must prevent snatching of ballot boxes and violence. “Elections must be conducted peacefully and in a hitch-free environment.  Details later… US institute wants SIECs scrapped 2019: Buhari proposes N242bn for INEC, security CAN: Politicians may set Nigeria on fire in 2019 if...